HEADWORD: Interradial
<hw>In`ter*ra"di*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Between the
radii, or rays; -- in Zoology, said of certain parts of radiate animals;
<as>as, the <ex>interradial</ex> plates of a starfish</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interramal</ent>⟦br⟧
